{
  "texts": [
    "This could range from spreading misinformation to leaking sensitive data.",
    "This risk becomes particularly pronounced when language models retrieve information from external sources that may contain maliciously injected prompts by attackers [36].",
    "These prompts are integrated into the model's context and influence its output.",
    "Arvind Narayanan, a Computer Science professor at Princeton University, demonstrated a striking example.",
    "He pointed out that any text on the internet could be manipulated to trigger inappropriate behaviour in AI models."
  ]
}